New Records: Spencer Schwellenbach and Simeon Woods Richardson started the game, marking the most combined letters in the last names of a starting pitching matchup with 28 letters.
Key Match Events: Atlanta Braves scored four times in the 10th inning to defeat the Minnesota Twins 8-6.
Matt Olson drove in the go-ahead run on a fielder’s choice.
Travis d’Arnaud added an RBI single.
Ramón Laureano put the game away with a two-run double.
Raisel Iglesias blew a save after allowing Trevor Larnach's game-tying RBI double.
Pierce Johnson allowed two runs in the 10th but struck out Matt Wallner with the tying run at first to end it.
Post-Match Reflections: Atlanta manager Brian Snitker said the win was costly but important.
Marcell Ozuna commented on the team's preparation and mindset.
Minnesota catcher Ryan Jeffers expressed frustration over the loss.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game went into extra innings.
The Twins have lost seven of their last nine games.
Atlanta holds the final wild-card spot in the NL.
